The map on morphisms is defined as post-composition: `homF f g = g ≫ f`.
For the identity `id Y`, we have `homF (id Y) g = g ≫ id Y`.
By the category law `comp_id`, `g ≫ id Y = g`.
The identity on `Hom c Y` (in `Type`) is just the identity function `id g = g`.
Thus, we need to show `g ≫ id Y = g`, which follows directly from `comp_id`.

